<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-238-254 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 834 805</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Jan 25 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Everex cuts 500, posts loss. (Everex Systems lays off 500employees)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Woods, Wendy.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Everex Systems Inc. (Layoffs).andO;Ticker:    EVRX.andO;Topic:     Computer industryLayoffLossesFourth Quarter.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>EVEREX CUTS 500, POSTS LOSS 01/25/91 FREMONT, CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1991 JAN 25(NB) -- Everex Systems has given walking papers to a fifth of its workforce,500 people, and says that it will post a loss of the quarter.andP;  The maker ofcomputers and peripherals expects to lose $7 to $10 million when the booksare finalized, the result of weak sales, gross margin pressure and highoperating costs, the company says.andM;Everex is currently developing a plan to reorganize some functions and todownsize all its major functions.andP;  Sales, reduction, engineering and othergroups are expected to be targeted in the reorganization.andM;President and CEO Steve Hui says &quot;It's a hard time for all of us at Everexand I deeply regret this action.&quot;andM;Everex says the layoffs will occur on February 4.andP;  The firm expects a loss ofbetween 30 cents and 50 cents per share in its second fiscal quarter.andM;(We dy Woods/19910125/Press Contact: Ann Butler, Everex, 415-498-1111)</TEXT></DOC>